# Frontend Patterns

## Jinja2 Templates
- All templates extend `base.html` via `{% extends "base.html" %}`
- Use `{% block content %}` for page-specific content
- Pass data via `TemplateResponse` — never inline JSON in templates

```python
# In router
from fastapi.templating import Jinja2Templates
templates = Jinja2Templates(directory="app/templates")

@router.get("/")
async def index(request: Request):
    return templates.TemplateResponse("index.html", {"request": request, "items": items})
```

## Bootstrap 5 Conventions
- Use Bootstrap utility classes; avoid custom CSS unless necessary
- Forms: use `form-control`, `form-label`, `mb-3` pattern
- Alerts: `alert alert-danger/success/info` for flash messages
- Layout: `container` > `row` > `col-*` grid

```html
<!-- Standard form field -->
<div class="mb-3">
  <label for="name" class="form-label">Name</label>
  <input type="text" class="form-control" id="name" name="name">
</div>
```

## HTMX (if needed for interactivity)
- Prefer HTMX over full JS frameworks for partial page updates
- Use `hx-get`, `hx-post`, `hx-target`, `hx-swap` attributes
- Return HTML fragments from endpoints when responding to HTMX requests
